VHyderabad Music Circle organised a vocal concert of noted vocalist T.Chandrabhanu at Kala Vedika of Thyagaraya Ganasabha. She was accompanied by T.C.Ananthakrishna on violin and A.Srinivas on mridangam, both well known in their respective fields. Chandrabhanu opened her recital with a Natakuranji Varnam in Aditalam which she rendered in Madhyamakalam and followed it with an invocationVara Vallabha Ramanain Hamsadhvani, a composition of GNB.This was followed byCheraraavademira Ramayyain Reetigowla, a rare composition in Adi Talam was rendered meaningfully.Latangiwas her firstragaessay which she handled with leisurely grace. Patnam Subramanya Iyyer&#8217;s compositionMariverein Khanda Chaputalamwas her choice which she rendered well. Thenerevalshe presented at the lineDharalona Nee Saatiwas quite exemplary , followed byswarakalpanapresented in twokalas(speeds).She then sangTelisi Rama Chintanato, another composition of Thyagaraja in Purnachandrika, as a preface for her main essay of the evening Thodi.Dasaradhireflectedthe melodic line of theragaperfectly. Thekirtanawas by itself an expressive presentation sticking to the norm of projectingsahityaflavourViolinist Ananthakrishna complemented the vocalist&#8217;s effort with his own imagination. Mridangist Srinivas came out with a laudable Tani avartanam.Both displayed authority on their respective instruments. Chandrabhanu presented   Ranjani, Sriranjani, Megharanjani and Janaranjani rendering the compositionRanjani Mrudu Pankaja Lochaniof Tanjavur Sankara Iyer in Aditalam.Each of theseragasin this Ranjanimaalahad a distinct appeal. Chandrabhanu rounded of her concert with akirtanaof Annamacharya -Ksheerabdi Kanyakakuin Kuranji, Khanda chapu talam, which is alsoMangalam,a concluding prayer.
